      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "Outgoing longwave radiation during the night will be quite good at times. The surface of the snowpack will soften quickly. Sunshine and high temperatures will give rise to increasing and thorough wetting of the snowpack below approximately 3000 m. <br/> West, north and east facing slopes above approximately 2500 m: Faceted weak layers exist in the bottom section of the old snowpack at elevated altitudes."
      },
